The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Row settled
                                                                                                                       7                                      Row settled
                      
	New Delhi: The Sports Ministry-IOA row over the tenure limit guidelines has been settled and both have agreed to work together with mutual respect and understanding, the International Olympic Committee said in a statement.         
	The tug-of-war between the Indian Olympic Association and the Sports Ministry over the guidelines  which fixes the term of the sports bosses in the country  had reached IOC, which claimed to have addressed the issue after a meeting with both the affected parties on Friday.         
	Calling it a fruitful meeting, the IOC said, During this meeting, all issues currently pending were discussed at length and settled. All parties agreed to work together with mutual respect and understanding... it said. (PTI)                                                                                                                     
